<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="365" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[809,1422,1490,1785]" pageId="6" pageNumber="365">
This species was previously recorded from Mt Nimba at Gouan (
<collectingCountry box="[1020,1108,1524,1550]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="6" pageNumber="365">Guinea</collectingCountry>
) and North Beeton (incorrectly given as ‘Bona’ by Wolton 
<emphasis box="[1219,1273,1557,1583]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="365">et al</emphasis>
., 1982) (
<collectingCountry name="Liberia" pageId="6" pageNumber="365">Liberia</collectingCountry>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="AELLEN, V." box="[896,1056,1591,1617]" pageId="6" pageNumber="365" pagination="629 - 638" refId="ref11916" refString="AELLEN, V. 1963. La Reserve Naturelle Integrale du Mont Nimba. XXIX. Chiropteres. Memoires de l'Institut Francais d'Afrique Noire, 66: 629 - 638." type="journal article" year="1963">Aellen, 1963</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="HILL, J. E." box="[1072,1199,1591,1617]" pageId="6" pageNumber="365" pagination="116 - 120" refId="ref13738" refString="HILL, J. E. 1982. Records of bats from Mount Nimba, Liberia. Mammalia, 46: 116 - 120." type="journal article" year="1982">Hill, 1982</bibRefCitation>
). Both individuals captured during this survey were emerging from mine adits on Mt Gangra, adjacent to Mt 
<collectingRegion box="[1303,1383,1658,1684]" country="Liberia" name="Nimba" pageId="6" pageNumber="365">Nimba</collectingRegion>
on the Liberian side (Monadjem 
<emphasis box="[1156,1207,1692,1718]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="365">et al</emphasis>
., 2013 
<emphasis box="[1287,1302,1692,1718]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="365">b</emphasis>
). The distribution of this species has recently been reviewed by 
<bibRefCitation author="FAHR, J." box="[846,1003,1759,1785]" pageId="6" pageNumber="365" pagination="391 - 392" refId="ref12553" refString="FAHR, J. 2013 a. Hipposideros marisae Aellen's leaf-nosed bat. Pp. 391 - 392, in The mammals of Africa. Volume IV: Hedgehogs, shrews and bats (M. HAPPOLD and D. C. D. HAPPOLD, eds.). Bloomsbury Publishing, London, 800 pp." type="book chapter" year="2013">
Fahr (2013 
<emphasis box="[976,991,1759,1785]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="365">a</emphasis>
)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
